endency is not required by the behavior wording.","test_description":"Send transcripts containing explicit decision statements to the real summarization model and assert those decisions are present in the `decisions` section and absent from narrative-only placement.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.02,"Integration":0.07,"System":0.03,"Agentic":0.74,"Workflow":0.14}},{"behavior_id":6,"description":"When the audio file is longer than 60 minutes, the service splits it into segments and processes them sequentially, merging the results into a single coherent summary.","minimum_level":"Workflow","justification":"This is explicitly a multi-step agentic sequence (segment -> transcribe/summarize per segment -> merge) where correctness depends on chained model outputs and handoff order/state. Integration is too low because it would miss model-output interaction across steps; System alone is too low because coherence depends on AI output quality, not just infrastructure.","test_description":"Run a real >60-minute recording through production segmentation, sequential STT/summary passes, and merge stage; assert all segments are processed in order and final summary remains coherent with preserved cross-segment action items/decisions.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.0,"Integration":0.02,"System":0.08,"Agentic":0.14,"Workflow":0.76}},{"behavior_id":7,"description":"The full pipeline (upload audio, transcribe, summarize, deliver structured output) completes without manual intervention for a real meeting recording.","minimum_level":"Workflow","justification":"Behavior explicitly requires full end-to-end pipeline over real recording with multiple agentic stages and stage-to-stage orchestration. Any lower level would miss failures in cross-stage sequencing, retries, and model-dependent transitions. Rejected Agentic/System because both are subsets of this explicitly multi-step pipeline